Jess Jackson, Owner of Racehorses Rachel Alexandra, Curlin, Dies at Age 81

-- B y   E b e n   N o v y - W i l l i a m s
-- 
2011-04-21T15:26:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-21/jess-jackson-owner-of-racehorses-rachel-alexandra-curlin-dies-at-age-81.html
Jess Jackson , owner of the
Preakness Stakes-winning filly  Rachel Alexandra , died at age 81
of cancer, according to a statement from his family.  Jackson, the founder of Kendall-Jackson winery, also owned
Curlin, winner of the Horse of the Year award in 2007 and 2008.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eben Novywilliams in New York at 
 enovywilliam@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  